The analytical skill data design encompasses how someone organizes information. Data strategy involves managing the people, processes, and tools used in data analysis. 

Analytical skills are the qualities and characteristics associated with using facts to solve problems.

An acquaintance tells you that they spend many hours each day “playing.” To learn more, you ask them whether they play sports, a musical instrument, or something else. Their answer helps you clarify the meaning of their statement. What does this scenario describe?
  This scenario describes understanding context. Context is the condition in which something exists or happens.

A technical mindset involves breaking things down into smaller steps and working with them in an orderly and logical way.

